DEPARTMENT: Call Center Operations
REPORTS TO: Call Center Operations Manager
STATUS: Full-Time or Part Time, Hourly
SCHEDULE: Various Available
 Hours of Operation: M-F 7:30 am to 5 pm
LOCATION: Remote Work or Central Office - 1850 W. Roosevelt Road

STATEMENT OF PURPOSE:
The Patient Access Representative is responsible for professionally answering phone calls from patients interested in scheduling an appointment with a physician, scheduling a medical test, or answering general questions related to the health system's services. The Patient Access Representative is also responsible for patient education with regard to available online services. The Patient Access Representative is expected to use online knowledge management tools (including EPIC) as resources to assist with patient calls and issue resolution. This is a call center environment and work hours may vary.

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES INCLUDE, BUT ARE NOT LIMITED TO:
Respond to telephone inquiries from patients with sensitivity and professionalism;
Listen without interruption to fully understand the needs of the patient;
Accurately schedule and register patients for appointments by utilizing the health system’s software and effectively communicate information with caller;
Maintain a current understanding of scheduling guidelines and registration procedures for use during patient calls;
Accurately secures patient demographics, insurance information, benefits and eligibility and updates into the health system’s software;
Use service recovery behaviors: offer appropriate apologies, explanations and resolutions.
Maintain up-to-date knowledge of the health system’s policies and procedures and use this knowledge when appropriate;
Adhere to the HIPAA (Privacy Act) as it relates to the confidentiality of information released
Perform other duties as assigned by Supervisor.

QUALIFICATIONS:
 High School diploma or equivalent required, Associate’s or Bachelor’s degree preferred;
 1 year of Healthcare and/or contact center experience required;
 Experience with Epic Software preferred
 Medical Terminology and/or medical insurance knowledge preferred
 Must be able to speak clearly and professionally, English required, bi-lingual (English/Spanish) a plus;
 Able to work with a database and navigate through a Windows environment required, e.g., logon/logoff, cut/copy/paste, minimize/maximize; knowledgeable of Microsoft outlook and Instant messaging
 Must be able to type a minimum of 35 words per minute ;
 Ability to effectively work within established contractual turnaround times;
 Demonstrated excellent interpersonal, communication, and multi-tasking skills;
 Proven ability to work as a member of a team;
 Ability to complete periodic program update training and successfully implement that knowledge in day to day operations;
Commitment to our mission of providing opportunities for people who are visually impaired, blind, deaf-blind, or blind with additional disabilities is essential.

The Chicago Lighthouse for People Who Are Blind or Visually Impaired is an Equal Opportunity Employer in full compliance with local, state, and federal Civil Rights & Affirmative Action laws. The Chicago Lighthouse for People Who Are Blind or Visually Impaired maintains a strong policy of accommodation and a consistent practice of employing qualified individuals with disabilities. All applicants will be afforded equal employment opportunity without discrimination because of race, color, religion, sex, marital status, national origin or ancestry, citizenship status, age, physical or mental disability unrelated to ability, sexual orientation, military status, order of protection status or unfavorable discharge from military service.

Masimo (NASDAQ: MASI) headquartered in Irvine, California, is a fast-growing and award-winning international medical technology and device company with operations spanning the globe. We develop innovative, noninvasive monitoring technologies that save, extend and improve the lives of people of all ages, in all walks of life. These revolutionary technologies are helping to solve "unsolvable" problems that have plagued the healthcare industry, while taking the pain and discomfort out of blood monitoring. For more than 25 years, innovation has been and will continue to be our passion.

To learn more about us, please visit: www.masimo.com

Job Summary

Clinical Account Executive is responsible for partnering with the Sr. Director Corporate Accounts, Directors, Corporate Accounts and Acute Care Sales Team in achieving individual and organizational sales goals. This position is part of the US Acute Care Sales Team directly reporting to the Director Corporate Accounts. The Clinical Account Executive works closely with the Sr. Director Corporate Accounts, Directors Corporate Accounts as well as the US Acute Care clinical and sales teams to coordinate all aspects of customer Sales, installations and training, research, project management including to identify and resolve challenges. The Clinical Account Executive is primarily a sales role, and also will be instrumental in helping the team effectively collaborate with Nurse, physician and clinical decision makers with the objective to insure that customer leadership recognizes how Masimo solutions and technology improve Patient Safety, Patient Quality, Patient Outcomes, Regulatory Requirements and nursing and/or clinical workflow.

Duties & Responsibilities

Engage with internal teams as a Clinical Sales leader in notable customer leadership presentations, and key evaluations, with a common sense of purpose, and a commitment to demonstrate how Masimo technologies can enhance caregiver workflow, improve patient and clinical outcome and/or comply with regulatory requirements;
Identify and target specific IDN’s for the sole purpose of obtaining specific sales goals as defined by senior sales management.
Act as lead conduit for all IDN RFPs and as liaison for contract negotiation and implementation.
Ensure maximum sales penetration through matrix of hospital leadership, GPO contact, Masimo senior sales and account management team.
Participate in IDN vendor fairs, conferences and act as strategic business partner for Masimo with IDN corporate.
Initiate, maintain and further develop all business relationships at the IDN corporate level, including existing and potential business partners.
Clinical and technology subject matter expert, able to articulate and champion Masimo solutions.
Evaluate trends in the industry, participate in developing and executing high level sales and marketing plans;
Foster strategic thinking and creativity to conceptualize innovative approaches to existing market opportunities in Acute Care, and new frontiers in the area of healthcare;
Participate with thought leaders in multiple areas including Acute Care, Tele-Medicine, trauma centers, and Hospital at Home organizations to promote improvements in patient care through the utilization of Masimo Technologies;
Partner with Sales leaders and account managers to achieve sales quota; Including Hospital Care, Tele-medicine and ambulatory surgery, and other areas as needed;
Manage or assist as needed with the installation process and personnel;
Participate in continued evaluation of new products and assist in beta testing and positioning;
Performs other duties or special projects as requested; Tiger Team.

Minimum Qualifications

Five or more years of sales experience in the IDN and GPO market, the clinical arena, with an understanding of Acute Care, and the US Continuum of Care; Leadership and operational experience is a plus.
Prior experience working as a Registered Nurse
Exceptional relationship building and negotiation skills.
Demonstrated experience in a similar role with strong relationships in hospital system at this level.
Proven success in sales within the medical device industry. (Preferred)
Must be able to professionally communicate effectively with management, executives, physicians, staff, peers, sales reps and customers;
The successful candidate must possess personal and professional credibility, and abide by Masimo’s guiding principles;
Commands strong, written, verbal communication and interpersonal skills;
Is comfortable in high visibility situations, exhibits strong self-confidence;
Must be comfortable with public speaking and developing clinical presentations;
Must be results oriented with positive “can do” attitude with a sense of urgency to get things done;
Must be comfortable in a business development role;
Has a proven track record in Change management, with an emphasis on new patient care processes based on clinical evidence and new, innovative technologies;
Must be able to build upon success of the organization’s existing customers;
Must be an independent problem solver;
Must be organized and detail oriented.

Preferred Qualifications

Possesses an deep understanding of the complex process of introducing clinically differentiated new technology into a price driven market;
Sales/management/business development experience;

Education

Bachelor’s degree. Clinical credentials as a Registered Nurse.

Physical requirements/Work Environment

This position primarily works outside of a traditional office, making frequent customer visits on a daily basis. Participates in all aspects of the installation and follow up of equipment in hospital and hospital like care facilities. Extensive and frequent domestic and local travel is a major job component, so the ability to operate a motor vehicle and maintain a valid Driver’s license is required. It also requires frequent driving, sitting, standing and walking. May stand for extended periods when facilitating customer meetings or walking in the facilities. Daily use of a computer and other computing and digital devices is required.

The physical demands of the position described herein are essential functions of the job and employees must be able to successfully perform these tasks for extended periods. Reasonable accommodations may be made for those individuals with real or perceived disabilities to perform the essential functions of the job described.

Masimo is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex including sexual orientation and gender identity, national origin, disability, protected Veteran Status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable federal, state or local law.

